FBIS4-38743 "drsov106_h_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 Moldova Turkey's Demirel Pledges `Broad Assistance' Turkey's Demirel Pledges `Broad Assistance' LD0106185094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1735 GMT 1 Jun 94 LD0106185094 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetsky] [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] 1 June TASS--Turkey is interested in Moldavia's [Moldova's] prosperity and territorial integrity and is ready to provide it with broad assistance, visiting Turkish President Suleyman Demirel said. In his address to the Moldavian Parliament on Wednesday, Demirel said that Turkish business circles are ready to invest in Moldavia's economy, especially its southern areas inhabited mostly by the Gagauz, Turkish-speaking minority. At the same time he stressed that the Gagauz must respect the territorial integrity of Moldavia. Demirel called for granting Gagauz areas special legal status. He pointed out that Turkey's interest in the Gagauz should be viewed as a sign of the big importance it attaches to territorial integrity, peace and economic and social development of Moldavia. The Gagauz people must become a bridge of friendship and cooperation, which will help in strengthening ties between the two nations, he said. Speaking about prospects for setting up an economic union of the Black Sea countries, the Turkish president said such a union would provide a new scheme of economic relations in the world. Demirel is in Kishinev on a three-day official visit. During the visit, the sides will sign a treaty of friendship and cooperation and discuss Turkish investments in the Moldavian economy.
